After almost two years, the light commercial vehicle market begins to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9,425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6 per cent compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decrease, according to the figures of the employers' union of the Anfac manufacturers and Ganvam, that of the dealers.
However, the good news should be nuanced, since the benchmark used for comparison in November 2008 was particularly poor, with a 60% decrease compared to the previous year.
